    tern:equipment """
    <h3 id="equipment">Equipment</h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      Mobile device (tablet/phone capable of taking high resolution photos) with
      the App<br />
      (progressive web app) saved to the home screen
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Trowel or small shovel</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Alcohol spray and small scrubbing brush</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      9 medium sized snap lock bags per plot (22 x 25 cm; white block for
      labelling)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>9 small calico bags per plot (ca. 15 x 20 cm)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>1 large calico bag for the plot (ca. 30 x 50 cm)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      ½ cup of mixed silica granules (10% self-indicating, 90% standard) per
      snap lock bag (prefilled)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Extra silica to allow for regular replacement</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      PPE for handling silica (protective eyeglasses, gloves and clothing;
      approved respirator if handling significant amounts or if irritation is
      experienced)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Adhesive voucher labels (with barcodes)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Permanent marker</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Trimble® R1 (GNSS receiver with sub-metre accuracy and Bluetooth
      connectivity).
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
    """^^rdf:HTML ;
    tern:instructions """
    <h3 id="instructions-and-procedures">Instructions and procedures</h3>
<ol type="1">
  <li>
    <p>
      Ensure the <em><a href="https://linkeddata.tern.org.au/viewers/dawe-vocabs?uri=https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/d15d05db-5007-411e-b257-105ef4f76821">Plot selection and layout</a></em> module has been completed to
      mark out the plot grid with sub-metre accuracy using the Trimble® R1,
      including the 25 x 25 m soil sub-site zone in the southwest corner of the
      plot (see <a href='#figure-1'>Figure 1</a>).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Select the ‘Soils’ module and then the ‘Soil metagenomics’ protocol in the
      App. The App will automatically record the <em>Plot name</em>, based on
      the established plot you are working in, the <em>Protocol</em>, and the
      <em>Date</em>.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Traverse the plot to familiarise yourself with the soils, terrain and
      microhabitats.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Locate nine sampling locations in different microhabitats, or
      microhabitats for a target species, taxa, or group across the plot, the
      first five with the soil sub-site zone and the remaining four spread
      across the plot (see <a href="#additional-guidelines">Additional guidelines</a> below).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li><p>For each surface sample, complete steps 6–16.</p></li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Select ‘Record soil metagenomics sample location’. The App will
      automatically record the
      <em>Metagenomics sub-site number</em> (sequentially from 1),
      <em>Easting</em>, <em>Northing</em>, <em>Zone</em>, <em>Datum</em> and
      location acquisition <em>Method</em> (i.e. ‘DGPS’).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Record who the metagenomic samples are <em>Collected by</em> from the
      drop-down list of personnel affiliated with your user login. Your
      selection will be prefilled for subsequent metagenomics sub-sites.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Record the <em>Microhabitat</em>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Select the ‘Microhabitat photo' button to capture an image of the
      microhabitat using your device's camera.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Brush any loose and obvious plant material and animal scats from the soil
      surface.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Use a trowel or small shovel (ensuring that it is not contaminated from
      another location) to remove approximately 200 g of the soil surface layer
      (maximum 3 cm depth).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Place this sample in a calico bag and label it with a barcode.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Select the 'Scan barcode' button to scan the barcode label on the sample
      and link the sample to the metagenomic sub-site.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Place the calico bag into a larger snap lock bag containing half a cup of
      mixed silica granules and seal the bag.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li><p>Record any Additional metagenomics soil sub-site comments.</p></li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Select 'Save metagenomics sub-site' to save the sub-site and return to the
      <em>Soil metagenomics</em> protocol.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li><p>Repeat steps 6–16 for each metagenomics sub-site.</p></li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Place each sealed zip-lock bag from the nine metagenomics sub-sites in the
      large calico bag for the plot and label this clearly with the plot number
      and date.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Select ‘Complete Soil metagenomics' to save the protocol and return to the
      <em><a href="https://linkeddata.tern.org.au/viewers/dawe-vocabs?uri=https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/6fd9d31f-9a77-4fc1-9eee-23ea8af32b95">Soils</a></em> module.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>
    """^^rdf:HTML ;
